721814f-a.folder: Mulberry Street & Prince Street., Manhattan, NY
721814f-a.text:
Mulberry Street, at, adjoining and north of the N. W. corner of Prince Street (left), showing prominently an old residence there. The corner structure is No. 47 Prince Street, while it's prototype is No 259 Mulberry Street. Adjoining the latter is a three story frame dwelling with a brick front. This is No. 261 Mulberry Street.
October 22, 1935
Berenice Abbott, photo
Federal Art Project

721813f-a.folder: Mulberry Street & Prince Street, Manhattan, NY
721813f-a.text:
(1)
Mulberry Street, at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of Prince Street. Also shown is Prince Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Mulberry Street. No. 261 Mulberry Street, north of the N.W. corner of Prince Street, is a 3-story frame house with a brick front.
December 21, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, slightly more inclusive. The 3-story building at the corner
is No. 47 Prince Street.
February 1924.
Eugene I  Armbruster Collection.

721815f-a.folder: Mulberry Street & Prince Street, Manhattan, NY
721815f-a.text:
Mulberry Street, west side, north from and including Prince, to and including Jersey Streets, showing prominently No. 47 Prince Street, a 3-story house, at the N.W. corner. Other buildings on this block bear Nos. 259, 261, 263-5 and 267 all on Mulberry Street. No. 261 is a 3-story frame house with a brick front. Shown on the left are the lower stories of a 6-story tenement house, No. 49-51 Prince Street. This set consists
of 2 views.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collectfon.

721816f-a.folder: Mulberry Street & Prince Street, Manhattan, NY
721816f-a.text:
Mulberry Street, at the N.E. corner of Prince Street, showing St. Patrick's R. C. Church. The cornerstone of this structure, formerly The Cathedral, was laid June 8, 1809 and consecrated by Bishop Cheverus of Boston, on May 4, 1815; it being completed in the latter year. In the churchyard is the tomub of Valentine Sherry. Here also are buried
Francis Delmonico and Stephen Jumel.
February 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
